accept_38001_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Since you have recently joined our school, you should walk around the temple and get to know your brothers.</font>
accept_38001_2=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Also, some scripts were stolen from the Sutra Pavilion. Please look into this matter for me.</font>
accept_38003_1=<font face="Default" color="#8fd6ef">(Jingneng's eyes show his intention to kill…)</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Hah. Don't you know that there is always someone stronger than you? Now I will fight you with all of my strength!</font>
accept_38004_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Qingzhi told me that some scripts from the Sutra Pavilion were stolen recently. We are not sure whether or not they were taken by someone from our own temple.</font>
accept_38006_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">I guess they were used by the thief who stole the script. Keep this to yourself for now. Jing De, who guards the outside area of Bodhi Hall, has a good relationship with Jingneng. See if he has any more information.</font>
accept_38008_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" ></font><font face="Default" color="#8fd6ef" >(Jing De keeps muttering to himself)</font>
accept_38009_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Evil monks managed to pass by the guards and attack? We must investigate this matter carefully. </font><font face="Default" color="#8fd6ef">(Examines Jing De)</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff"> Jing De has been given a strange poison. Take him to Master Xuan Cheng quickly!</font>
accept_38010_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">The poison is strange... I have never seen it before. It is worrying that he is still unconscious.</font>
accept_38011_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Jing De has been given a revival pill to briefly delay the poison from spreading more. Fetch clean water from the Lotus Pool so I can prepare more medicine for him.</font>
accept_38012_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">All monks should be merciful. We will try to save him, but if we cannot find the antidote...</font>
accept_38014_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">We have no more information right now, but the suspicious monk was captured. You can interrogate him if you wish.</font>
accept_38015_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">What? Uh... I... I don't have the antidote. There is no antidote for this poison! Haha…</font>
accept_38018_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">You Shaolin monks care too much about being merciful. In any case, I will say nothing more.</font>
accept_38019_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" > </font>
accept_38022_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" > </font>
accept_38025_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >The antidote is in my shoes. Take</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >…</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >it out…and let me take it…</font>
accept_38027_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >   </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >“Instead of the bottom Chinese character component of Liang, there is the bottom component Ding. That is a new Chinese character Ting. The location where they will exchange scriptures is Fresh Wind Pavilion. I have told you all. Please help me to take the antidote as soon as possible……</font>
accept_38027_2=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >A pair of Huoyun Poison Palms from my elder brother are enough for you.</font>
accept_38028_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >You know too much for me to let you live.</font>
accept_38029_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">I am sorry. There is nothing we can do. Go and report Jing De's death to the abbot.</font>
accept_38030_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Younger Brother, please report this situation to the abbot.</font>
accept_38032_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >   </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >Hey, I have no way to save him. Only</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" > antidote from the one who poisoned Jingde</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" > can</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" > save his life</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >……</font>
accept_38034_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Greed, anger, and indulgence are three sins we must always avoid. Purify yourself of these evils, so you can help purify others. I hope that you learn from Jing De and Jingneng's misfortunes.</font>
accept_38036_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Fate guided the events involving Jing De and Jingneng, so you should not feel responsible for the outcome. Learning martial arts must be supported by cultivation of Zen, or like Jingneng you will lose self-control and become evil.</font>
accept_38037_1=<s><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Don't waste my time asking me questions, I won't tell you anything.</font>
complete_38001=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Ow... I did not expect you to be so skilled in martial arts.</font>
complete_38003=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">What do you want me to store away for you?</font>
complete_38004=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">What is this? Where did you find these?</font>
complete_38006=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">I stole the script</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff"></font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">. No one else was involved. </font><font face="Default" color="#8fd6ef">(Jing De passes out.)</font>
complete_38008=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">What </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">happened to </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Jing De?</font>
complete_38009=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Jing De is suffering from a very rare poison. Even if you could get some snow lotus from Mount Tianshan, I am still not sure whether I can save him.</font>
complete_38010=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">The only way to save Jing De is to find the man who poisoned him and get the antidote from them. There is no other way to save him.</font>
complete_38011=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Thank you, Young Nephew. Now, if you want to help save Jing De's life, you must find the man who poisoned him and get the antidote.</font>
complete_38012=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">A Dharma Hall disciple came across a suspicious monk, but I do not know what he has been doing here.</font>
complete_38014=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Ha. Again they send someone else, and your efforts too will be in vain. I won't tell you anything!</font>
complete_38015=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">You waste your breath. I won't say anything more.</font>
complete_38018=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" > </font>
complete_38019=<s><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Shaolin is known for showing mercy. If I refuse to tell you anything and you kill me, your reputation will...</font>
complete_38022=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">   </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">You forced me to take the drug! Antidote! Give me the antidote! I don't want to die.</font>
complete_38025=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">You've got the antidote. Please </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">give me the green pill </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">and let me take it.</font>
complete_38025_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">This purple pill can detoxify Jingde's poison, and this white one can temporarily enhance your skills.</font>
complete_38027=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">   </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">What's the matter? I'm on good terms with Shaolin disciples. I'm waiting for the Advanced Monk of Prajna Hall to discuss about the Buddhist Scriptures.</font>
complete_38028=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff"> This is really the missing script! Thank you for your help.</font>
complete_38029=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">We reap what we sow. Zu Ming's intentions in training his disciples are good, but neglects their need to learn proper cultivation of the mind.</font>
complete_38030=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">What? He is unconscious again? </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">This...</font>
complete_38032=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Amitabha. </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">I wish Jingneng could bear Buddha in his mind after he pulled through this mishap.</font>
complete_38034=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Greed will make people lose their way, and they will become victims of their own evil deeds.</font>
complete_38036=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Study both martial arts and Zen diligently, but never forget Zen and indulge yourself in the martial arts. Remember this lesson well.</font>
complete_38037=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">He is acting very cold to me. I usually get along well with other monks, so what is his problem?</font>
context_38001=Abbot Xuanhuai has asked you to familiarize yourself with the temple and your new brothers.
context_38003=Jingneng is behaving strangely... I think he knows something about the missing scripts. Another nearby Elder Brother may be able to help.
context_38004=Jingneng is a disciple of Zu Ming. Zutong has a disciple named Jing De. He and Jingneng have a close friendship. Find Zu Ming yourself and tell him about it.
context_38006=Zu Ming thinks the thief used the veil and scarf in the box to cover his face. But if Sutra Pavilion is well-guarded, how did the thief get in and steal the scripts?
context_38008=<s>Jing De was attacked by evil monks. I repelled them, but he was poisoned in the assualt.
context_38009=Jing De was poisoned and needs medical attention. Go and ask Master Xuan Cheng for help.
context_38010=Master Xuan Cheng can do nothing to stop the poison within Jing De. In his opinion, only the person who poisoned Jing De can save him.
context_38011=Master Xuan Cheng needs to make Jing De more revival pills. Go fetch water from the Lotus Pool beside the bridge of the Lixue Pavilion.
context_38012=The Abbot was just informed that some Foreign Monks were found nearby. Are they?from the group who attacked Jing De? Were they involved with the stolen scripts? I must find out more from Liao Yin Immortal.
context_38014=Liao Yin Immortal said that?they have caught a suspicious monk and handed him over to Qing Yuan, but the captive monk has refused to talk. He was one of people who attacked Jing De. When the Lama was asked for an antidote, he said there was no antidote for this kind of poison.
context_38018=The captive Lama is very stubborn, and he refuses to yield any more information. How can the riddle in the Secret Letter be deciphered?
context_38022=<s>The arrested Lama is stubborn. Search the left poison from his body. Serve him with the same sauce.
context_38025=<s>The poison was fed to the Lama and he said the antidote is kept in his shoe. Speak to Elder Brother Qingyuan.
context_38027=<s>The Western Lama has admitted he is not alone here. He has some fellows somewhere. The answer of the puzzle is the Qingfeng Pavilion at the east of the Bodhidharma Hall. Watch out the Lama who is the connecter there.
context_38028=Another suspicious monk is in the Clean Wind Pavilion, and may be waiting to meet with his accomplice. Subdue him and ask how the script was stolen.
context_38029=Jing De fell into a coma again. Master Xuan Cheng said that Jing De had died, and told Zu Ming and the abbot of the news.
context_38030=The evil monks who stole scripts have been arrested, and the abbot will decide their punishment. Go quickly to Jing De, who is awake but weak.
context_38032=Jingde went into a coma again. It is lucky that I always took along the Antidote from West Monk. Hard work pays off. Finally Jingde was saved.
context_38034=Was it fate or a man-made disaster for Jing De and Jingneng? Listen to Abbot Xuanhuai.
context_38036=Was it fate or a man-made disaster for Jing De and Jingneng? Listen to Abbot Xuanhuai.
context_38037=The puzzle says, "There are few lightspots but a little star." Is that place connected to exchanging the stolen Skill Script? I need to ask more people for their interpretations of this riddle.
context_38049=<s>A disciple reported to me that Elder Zuneng got into trouble outside the temple gate. Go see.
menu_38001_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Thank you, I will.</font>
menu_38001_2=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Yes, Abbot.</font>
menu_38003_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Jingneng, please calm down…</font>
menu_38004_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">When I fought with Elder Brother Jingneng, a script fell from beneath his robes and he became very flustered. His behavior was very suspicious….</font>
menu_38006_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff" >Thank you, Shifu. I</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" > will head that way immediately.</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff" ></font>
menu_38008_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">I should take Jing De to the abbot for help.</font>
menu_38009_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Abbot, you are right.</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff"> We will go now</font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">.</font>
menu_38010_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Master, wait a moment. I am going to visit Jing De.</font>
menu_38011_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Yes, I will go now.</font>
menu_38012_1=<font face="Default" color="#8fd6ef">(I will report this to the abbot before I do anything else...)</font>
menu_38014_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">That is good to hear, thank you.</font>
menu_38015_1=<font face="Default" color="#8fd6ef">(The monk looks inside his clothing subconsciously while speaking...) </font><font face="Default" color="#ffffff">Why are you suddenly so nervous? Stop lying to me!</font>
menu_38018_1=<font face="Default" color="#ffffff">There is so much hate in your heart! </font><font face="Default" color="#8fd6ef">(If I cannot get him to talk, then what can I do?)</font>
